# agent *(working name)*

A guardrail-**detection kernel** — tiny classifiers (prompt-injection, PII, secrets,
toxicity/jailbreak) compiled into **portable, signed WASM artifacts** that run
anywhere: embedded via **wasmtime** in a Rust/Go/Python service, in an edge worker,
in a proxy hot path, in a browser. One artifact, one frozen ABI, identical verdicts
everywhere. **It detects and cites; it never decides** — policy (block/redact/route)
belongs to the embedding host or control plane (⟐ the Go `operator` suite), never to
this kernel. This file is the operating manual — read it every session.

**Scope: the kernel and its artifacts, not a guardrail service.** The guardrail
market is saturated at the service/library layer (Lakera, llm-guard, NeMo
Guardrails); nobody ships the detector as a portable artifact. **The wedge is the
packaging, not the classifier.** If a change turns this repo into one more hosted
guardrail service — or puts policy logic in the kernel — the design is wrong.

**Why this exists (the three differentiators, ROADMAP §0):**
(1) **agnostic by ABI** — a new detector, inference technique, or host language is a
new artifact or SDK behind the frozen contract, zero kernel changes; (2)
**deterministic, local, private — by construction** — the sandbox exposes no clock,
no randomness, no network, no filesystem, so an artifact *cannot* be flaky or phone
home; same input + same artifact = same verdict on every host; (3) **the moat is
packaging + the feed** — the stable ABI/toolchain, signed content-addressed
distribution, and (open-core) a continuously retrained artifact feed; the runtime,
toolchain, and reference detectors stay OSS forever.

## Repo layout

```
crates/
  abi/        `agent-abi` — the contract: the Detector ABI (versioned) + the canonical
              `Verdict` wire type (labels, scores, byte-offset spans, provenance:
              detector id + semver + threshold + scorecard hash). Serde-stable,
              #[non_exhaustive], additive-only.
  host/       `agent-host` — the runtime: wasmtime embedding with fuel metering, memory
              limits, epoch interruption; deterministic linker (no WASI clocks/random/
              net/fs); pooled instantiation + module caching. The one engine every
              surface drives.
  cli/        the `agent` binary. `agent check` (detect on text/files/stdin), later
              `agent pull` (signed artifacts) and `agent serve` (loopback sidecar).
detectors/    artifact SOURCES (Rust → wasm32), one directory per detector, each with
              an `agent.toml` manifest (budgets, labels) + `cases/` golden verdicts.
              mock/ is the permanent keyless fixture; secrets/ pii/ injection/ follow.
xtask/        dev orchestration — `cargo xtask ci` runs the full local gate, including
              building every detector to wasm and running its goldens. Never shipped.
```

## Guardrails (non-negotiable)

1. **Detects, never decides.** The kernel returns cited `Verdict`s with lossless
   spans; block/allow, redaction, routing, and tenant policy live in the embedding
   host (⟐ operator). Policy code in this repo is a design smell (ROADMAP Phase 11
   tombstone).
2. **Deterministic by absence.** The linker exposes nothing beyond the ABI: no
   clocks, no randomness, no network, no filesystem. An artifact importing anything
   else fails to load. Never "temporarily" add an import to unblock a detector.
3. **No LLM code, no model keys.** Detectors are tiny local models inside artifacts;
   the kernel never calls a model API. LLM-as-judge is someone else's product.
4. **Measured, not marketed.** Every shipped detector carries a **CI-generated
   scorecard** (precision/recall on public corpora); hand-written accuracy claims
   are forbidden; a quality regression fails the gate like an API break.
5. **No secrets, anywhere.** There is no API key in the detection path by design —
   a change that needs one is mis-scoped. Fixture corpora contain **synthetic**
   credentials only, never real ones (not even revoked).
6. **Artifacts are source.** Detector wasm is built by the gate from in-repo source
   and signed at release — never hand-committed binaries. Same inputs → same
   artifact hash.

## Conventions

- **Rust**, stable, one workspace. Keep `agent-abi` dependency-light so the contract
  is cheap to depend on from anywhere.
- The wire contract is sacred: `Verdict` JSON field names + exit codes (`0` clean ·
  `1` detection fired · `2`+ operational error) are golden-tested; evolution is
  additive-only (new optional fields; never rename/remove/retype).
- Every detector ships with `cases/` goldens; every metric with known-answer tests.
  Pure logic is tested against known inputs, never live data.
- No-panic discipline: `unwrap`/`expect`/`panic!` denied outside tests. A hostile
  artifact, fuel exhaustion, or malformed input is a typed value that degrades to a
  clear message.
- Config is layered **flags > env (`AGENT_*`) > file (TOML) > defaults**; `tracing`
  logs to stderr; stdout is verdicts only, so `agent check … 2>/dev/null` stays
  pipe-clean.
- `cargo xtask ci` must be green before anything is considered done (fmt · clippy
  `-D warnings` · build · test · docs · feature powerset · deny · artifact goldens —
  keyless, offline).
- **Git is human-driven.** The user makes every commit and push; the **coding
  agent** (Claude, Gemini, Codex — as opposed to `agent`, this project) never runs
  `git commit` / `git push` (or any other CI-triggering action). The coding agent's
  job ends at: changes made, gate green, roadmap box checked in the working tree,
  and — **only when asked** — a commit message drafted (imperative subject,
  reference the P-ID, never an AI co-author/attribution trailer).

## Build order (roadmap)

The phase-by-phase plan is the single source of truth in **`ROADMAP.md`** (13
sequentially-gated phases; its **checkboxes are the state**). Work it per its §0.5
working loop: first unchecked box in ID order, one item per iteration, gate green, and
the box checked **together with the work** so they land in one commit (message
references the ID, e.g. `P3.2: deterministic linker — no WASI imports`). The
**user** makes that commit. Never start a phase before the prior one's Exit gate
passes. The repo's prior contents (a retired trading-engine project) are removed by
P1.1 — audit nothing, inherit nothing. Don't duplicate phase status here — update
the roadmap. Hard-to-reverse choices land as dated entries in `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
